# Performance Concern Atom
concern: performance
triggers: ["성능", "느림", "최적화", "빠르게", "메모리", "performance", "optimize", "speed"]
load_when: performance or optimization mentioned

## Core Principle
MEASURE FIRST, THEN OPTIMIZE. Never optimize without profiling data.

## Runtime Optimization Rules
- Use generators/streams for large data sets (memory savings)
- Object pooling to reduce GC pressure
- CI caching, parallel builds, remove unnecessary files
- Measure (profile) before ANY optimization

## Data Processing Patterns
|Scenario|Forbidden|Recommended|
|------|------|------|
|Large DB query|Load all results into array/list|Cursor/stream row-by-row|
|Large file read|Load entire file into memory|Line-by-line streaming|
|Collection iteration|Create intermediate arrays|Generator / lazy evaluation|
|API pagination|Unbounded full data query|Page/cursor-based, enforce max limit|
|Bulk Insert/Update|Row-by-row repeated queries|Batch processing (bulk insert, chunk update)|
|Loop object creation|New object per iteration|Declare outside loop or reuse object pool|
|DB connections|New connection per request|Connection pool mandatory, explicit max pool size|
|Large responses|Generate all then send|Chunked streaming response|
|Repeated queries|DB/API call every time|TTL-based caching (read-only data first)|
|Large payload|Uncompressed|gzip/brotli compression|

## Memory Optimization Command
Trigger: `optimize memory usage of <module>`
1. Profile to identify bottlenecks
2. Analyze memory allocation patterns
3. Propose optimization (pool, streaming, lazy)
4. Re-measure and compare

## Build Optimization
- Bundlers: esbuild, tsup, Rollup (tree-shaking)
- Memory limits: `--max-old-space-size` (Node), container limits
- Large data: Stream API, Generator, Readable streams

